    "body":  {
                 "storage":  {
                                 "value":  "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUser Story\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAs a\u003c/strong\u003e system user\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eI want to\u003c/strong\u003e be able to update existing Payment\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSo that \u003c/strong\u003eI have the possibility to correct my mistake or change the conditions for the Payment\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cu\u003eDesign:\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://xd.adobe.com/view/da11392b-b666-46e7-b12c-44e30f397637-8f42/\" data-card-appearance=\"inline\"\u003ehttps://xd.adobe.com/view/da11392b-b666-46e7-b12c-44e30f397637-8f42/\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAcceptance criteria:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;Check system user permissions to see edit icon on Payment listing/detail page. If no such permission, edit icon will be disabled\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eEditing Payment\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eAllows to edit all Payment in the system\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eClicking on an edit icon on Payment listing or detail page will allow edit mode\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003eIf \u003c/span\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003eAccounting Period\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003e was closed and user wants to edit payment, in this case editing operation should be forbidden even if user has respective permission (Editing Payment). Blockings should be always editable\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003eIf \u003c/span\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003ePayment Package\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color: rgb(7,71,166);\"\u003e was locked and user wants to edit payment, in this case editing operation should be forbidden even if user has respective permission (Editing Payment). Blockings should be always editable\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eAdditionally should be checked if payment is connected to any receivable or liability; \u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eif connected shouldn\u0026rsquo;t be able to edit payment related data (all sub-objects and fields before Blocked for offsetting\u0027s shouldn\u0026rsquo;t be editable )\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eif user has permission to edit \u0027Blocked for offsetting\u0027 permission should allow to edit related fields\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eBlocked from date\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eBlocked to date\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eReason\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eAdditional information\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eif payment is not connected to any receivable or liability should allow to edit payment object with following logic:\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNumber\u003c/strong\u003e should stay disabled and it is not possible to edit\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDate of full offset - \u003c/strong\u003ealways disable (filled automatically by offsetting process)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCurrent amount - \u003c/strong\u003ealways disable (filled automatically by offsetting process)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn Payment to edit  \u003cstrong\u003eBlocked for offsetting\u003c/strong\u003e sections, user should have relevant permission \u0026lsquo;Blocked for offsetting\u0026rsquo;:\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf user does not have such permissions, checkboxes should be disabled (related fields should stay disabled as well - Blocked from date, Blocked to date, Reason and Additional Information)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSub-objects:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eCustomer - can be edited, firstly should remove\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eBilling group - can be edited, firstly should remove\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eOutgoing document - can be edited, firstly should remove\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eReceivable and liabilities offsetting - can\u0026rsquo;t be edited \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eClicking on \u0027\u003cstrong\u003eSave\u003c/strong\u003e\u0027 button will update Payment\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eSystem will check all validations and if successful will save changes, else error\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen clicking on \u0027\u003cstrong\u003eCancel\u003c/strong\u003e\u0027 or \u0027\u003cstrong\u003eX\u003c/strong\u003e\u0027 button should check changes and if there are changes made then warning pop-up message comes out with button: \u0027Your changes are not saved, are you sure you want to cancel?\u0027 Yes/No\u003c/p\u003e\u003col start=\"1\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eYes - will close payment editing page and return to listing page\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eNo - will close warning pop-up and stay on payment editing page\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eWarning message should be managed from the system settings\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003eAudit Log record should be created\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e",
                                 "representation":  "storage",
